# Walkthrough: [/api/match.js](file:///f:/Extention/Resume/api/match.js) Endpoint

## What Was Built

A new Vercel serverless function at [match.js](file:///f:/Extention/Resume/api/match.js) that computes **semantic similarity** between resume text and a job description.

## How It Works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Ext as Chrome Extension
    participant Match as /api/match
    participant OAI as OpenAI API
    Ext->>Match: POST { resumeText, jobDescription }
    Match->>OAI: Batch embeddings (2 inputs)
    OAI-->>Match: 2 × 1536-dim vectors
    Match->>Match: Cosine similarity → percentage
    Match-->>Ext: { matchScore: 82 }
```

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Model** | `text-embedding-3-small` (cheapest, ~$0.02/1M tokens) |
| **API call** | Single batch call for both inputs |
| **Dependencies** | Zero — native `fetch` + pure JS cosine similarity |
| **CORS** | `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` (same pattern as [generate.js](file:///f:/Extention/Resume/api/generate.js)) |
| **Env var** | `OPENAI_API_KEY` (must be set in Vercel dashboard) |

## Changes Made

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| [match.js](file:///f:/Extention/Resume/api/match.js) | **Created** — new endpoint |
